<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870212-0128 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Omnicom Group Inc.</HL><DD> 02/12/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WNEWS OMCM </IN><DATELINE> OMNICOM GROUP INC. (New York)  </DATELINE><TEXT>    Thomas Watson, 52 yearsold, was named president and chief operating officer of thediversified agency services division of this advertisingholding company. He will be in charge of Omnicom's 15specialty businesses, which include public relations, directmarketing and sales promotion. He assumes theresponsibilities formerly held by Stephen B. Oresman, 55, whowas recently named corporate administrative officer for theparent. Mr. Watson had been corporate coordination directorduring the formation of Omnicom through a merger of threeadvertising agencies and was previously a senior vicepresident at BBDO International Inc., one of the agencies.</TEXT></DOC>